Within the oxic oligotrophic sediments, the activity is generally low but it may increase by several orders of magnitude depending on the lithology .

Under the deeper anoxic conditions, the terminal electron acceptors are used in sequential series, according to the free energy yield of the redox reactions, starting from nitrate reduction and denitrification, to dissimilatory Mn(IV) and Fe(III) reduction, to sulfate reduction and finally to methanogenesis, which is of primary importance to the DCO Deep Life mission .
