In this section we will discuss recent work on the evolution of organisms resistant to pressures that are far beyond the pressure limits currently experienced by organisms on Earth.

researchers from the Geophysical Laboratory in Washington DC reported a remarkable result that samples of E. coli and S. oneidensis showed signs of metabolic activity at pressures extending into the GPa range (1.4-1.7 GPa), mainly based on in-situ Raman spectroscopic investigations of product/reactant ratios .
