Other remarkable survival stories concern the exposure of bacterial organisms to shock conditions.

It is well known that impacts from comets and meteorites, including ejecta from other planets as well as non-planetary bodies, have influenced the chemical evolution of Earth, and investigations or speculations about these extra-solar bodies or remnants of early solar system components have instigated theories of “panspermia” and possible origins of life elsewhere in the universe with subsequent transportation to early Earth .
